<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/c81c6b7e6faf54942eb0b36a2a55861a.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 4 and b = 8. Calculate:</p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>8.9</li><li>26.6</li><li>63.4</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={4}^{{2}}+{8}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={16}+{64}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={80}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{80}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{8.9442719099992}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{8.9}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arctan{{\left(\frac{{4}}{{8}}\right)}}}\approx{26.565051177078}\approx{26.6}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{26.565051177078}^{\circ}\approx{63.434948822922}\approx{63.4}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

